Updated the getNBackLevel function to map difficulty levels 1–10 to N-back levels 1 through 5 (previously capped at 3). The new mapping is: difficulty 1–2 → 1-back, 3–4 → 2-back, 5–6 → 3-back, 7–8 → 4-back, 9–10 → 5-back. The sequence generation comment was also updated to reflect the expanded range. No backend changes were needed since the adaptive difficulty service controls the difficulty value (1–10) which is then mapped to the N-back level in the frontend.